1
00:00:05,942 --> 00:00:08,567
♫ I want to go to the future ♫

2
00:00:08,567 --> 00:00:12,122
♫  Time bears witness to my quirkiness  ♫

3
00:00:12,122 --> 00:00:18,315
♫  I want to seize the day and put the whole world into my head  ♫

4
00:00:18,315 --> 00:00:24,541
♫  I want to go back in time to do all the crazy things I didn't do  ♫

5
00:00:24,541 --> 00:00:30,160
♫  Don't say goodbye, don't be in a daze, let my radiant light be bright  ♫

6
00:00:30,862 --> 00:00:35,948
♫  We are always looking forward to the unknown future  ♫

7
00:00:35,948 --> 00:00:42,148
♫  And often overlooking our surroundings and best plan in front of us  ♫

8
00:00:43,215 --> 00:00:48,272
♫ Every day my heart beats for you ♫

9
00:00:48,272 --> 00:00:49,885
♫  Be your light  ♫

10
00:00:49,885 --> 00:00:54,648
♫  You are no doubt irreplaceable  ♫

11
00:00:55,548 --> 00:01:02,048
♫ Every day the sun shines through the window ♫

12
00:01:02,048 --> 00:01:07,115
♫  With your reflection being my incredible highlight  ♫

13
00:01:08,582 --> 00:01:11,902
[I Don't Want to be Brothers with You]

14
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:15,587
My mom's back?

15
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:25,659
- I'll go get the door.
- Wait a minute.

16
00:01:25,659 --> 00:01:28,540
Well, straighten out your jacket

17
00:01:28,540 --> 00:01:30,405
and wipe your mouth.

18
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:39,389
The door isn't locked. Come in.

19
00:01:42,008 --> 00:01:44,340
Uncle Gao, happy Mid-Autumn Festival!

20
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:46,800
Beibei, Doudou, happy Mid-Autumn Festival!

21
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,640
- Doudou, recite the poem.
- "Autumn is a wonderful season of cool breezes.

22
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:51,219
May the Mid-Autumn moon remain the same every year.

23
00:01:51,219 --> 00:01:53,200
I wish you all a happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

24
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,020
May you be showered with joyous occasions!"

25
00:01:55,020 --> 00:01:57,339
Doudou, you're terrific!

26
00:01:57,339 --> 00:01:59,319
Uncle Gao, my dad asked me to bring this to you.

27
00:01:59,319 --> 00:01:59,879
Okay, thank you.

28
00:01:59,879 --> 00:02:03,079
Come on, Gao Yang, give Beibei the dumplings and moon cakes.

29
00:02:03,079 --> 00:02:04,719
No, that's alright. We have them at home.

30
00:02:04,719 --> 00:02:06,580
It's okay. Let Old Jin try my cooking, too.

31
00:02:06,580 --> 00:02:08,580
- I made them.
- Sure.

32
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:10,580
- Xiaowen, happy Mid-Autumn Festival!
- Happy Mid-Autumn Festival!

33
00:02:10,580 --> 00:02:11,700
Thank you.

34
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:13,300
Doudou, take this.

35
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,740
- We're going upstairs now.
- Okay,

36
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:15,740
- bye.
- Bye.

37
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:18,380
- Happy Mid-Autumn Festival!
- Happy Mid-Autumn Festival!

38
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:23,923
Let's eat.

39
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:41,020
Gao Yang, stop pulling a long face.

40
00:02:41,020 --> 00:02:44,439
Are you mad that your mom didn't come to see you?

41
00:02:44,439 --> 00:02:46,096
No.

42
00:02:46,096 --> 00:02:49,360
Anna didn't handle this properly.

43
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,580
She promised to bring you to Beijing before.

44
00:02:51,580 --> 00:02:53,420
She didn't come or apologize to you.

45
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:55,219
Now that she's in Tieyuan,

46
00:02:55,219 --> 00:02:58,039
even if she's not celebrating the holiday with us, she should at least come visit you.

47
00:02:58,039 --> 00:03:00,559
Maybe she's too busy.

48
00:03:00,559 --> 00:03:02,219
Xiaowen is right.

49
00:03:02,219 --> 00:03:03,939
That's how Anna is.

50
00:03:03,939 --> 00:03:05,939
She has no time for anything else when she's working.

51
00:03:05,939 --> 00:03:08,339
Back then, we didn't celebrate New Years, holidays, or anything.

52
00:03:08,339 --> 00:03:11,439
- I'll talk to her later.
- You don't have to comfort me.

53
00:03:12,239 --> 00:03:14,099
I've thought it through.

54
00:03:14,099 --> 00:03:16,499
I'm not important to her at all.

55
00:03:16,499 --> 00:03:17,939
She doesn't even want this family anymore.

56
00:03:17,939 --> 00:03:19,339
Why would she want me?

57
00:03:19,339 --> 00:03:21,759
Yangyang, don't think that way.

58
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:24,373
I'm fine, really.

59
00:03:25,819 --> 00:03:29,720
Well, from now on, the three of us will live together. Okay?

60
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,059
I'm fine. Let's eat.

61
00:03:31,059 --> 00:03:33,619
Sure, the three of us will live together.

62
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:42,799
Let's eat, let's eat. Xiaowen, eat.

63
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:51,119
- The dumplings are pretty good.
- Right?

64
00:03:53,390 --> 00:03:55,970
[Happiness For the Whole Family]

65
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:06,780
Hello, may I ask where Mr. Gao Bin live?

66
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:08,180
You're looking for Mr. Gao?

67
00:04:08,180 --> 00:04:09,792
I'm looking for Gao Yang.

68
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,420
He's upstairs. I'll take you up there.

69
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:14,366
Okay, thank you.

70
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:25,779
Gao Yang, I asked you to carry the plate and you dropped it!

71
00:04:25,779 --> 00:04:27,800
What else can you do?

72
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,579
This is so dirty!

73
00:04:30,940 --> 00:04:33,799
Mr. Gao, someone's here for Gao Yang.

74
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:37,460
Who is it? Who's looking for me?

75
00:04:38,339 --> 00:04:40,234
Why did you come to my house?

76
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,560
We have money.

77
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,763
You don't need to bribe us.

78
00:04:46,979 --> 00:04:49,600
Gao Yang, this is from your mom.

79
00:04:53,860 --> 00:04:56,910
[Wedding Invitation from Anna and Zhan Chonghai]

80
00:04:58,020 --> 00:04:59,799
My mom is getting married?

81
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:02,080
Wait... This...

82
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:05,307
An... An... Anna...

83
00:05:05,307 --> 00:05:06,999
How... how... How is she getting married?

84
00:05:06,999 --> 00:05:08,124
To who?

85
00:05:08,124 --> 00:05:09,620
You don't know him.

86
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:12,179
- I'm leaving now.
- Wait a minute. Explain it first.

87
00:05:12,179 --> 00:05:14,539
Why did Anna tell me she's getting married?

88
00:05:14,539 --> 00:05:17,520
Is she a-a-asking me for a wedding gift?

89
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,839
Director An didn't invite you.

90
00:05:18,839 --> 00:05:20,799
She only invited Gao Yang.

91
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:30,919
Do you have any other questions?

92
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:33,920
Why did she notify Gao Yang?

93
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,299
To... To attend her wedding?

94
00:05:35,299 --> 00:05:37,216
To recognize a new dad?

95
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:40,959
Gao Yang, I'll come and pick you up on the day of the wedding.

96
00:05:40,959 --> 00:05:42,677
Where's my mom?

97
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:47,460
Director An has already returned to Beijing.

98
00:05:47,460 --> 00:05:49,500
She'll come back to take care of things on the National Day.

99
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,700
Don't lie to me. She must be downstairs.

100
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:54,520
- Gao Yang, Gao Yang!
- Wait, no, come here.

101
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,160
Let me ask you.

102
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:55,759
Gao Yang!

103
00:05:55,759 --> 00:05:57,439
When did Anna get engaged?

104
00:05:57,439 --> 00:05:58,660
When did she get engaged?

105
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,280
Gao Yang! Gao Yang, what are you doing?

106
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,480
Stay out of this.

107
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:03,099
Auntie already went back to Beijing.

108
00:06:03,099 --> 00:06:05,077
I know her very well.

109
00:06:06,419 --> 00:06:08,280
Come out now! I can see you!

110
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,440
Come out!

111
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:11,100
What are you knocking for?

112
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:13,339
Would anyone talk to their mother this way?

113
00:06:13,339 --> 00:06:14,700
Aren't you already here?

114
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:16,480
Why didn't you go upstairs?

115
00:06:18,219 --> 00:06:20,357
I don't want to see Gao Bin.

116
00:06:23,179 --> 00:06:24,765
Who is this?

117
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,280
My buddy Ye Xiaowen.

118
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:29,115
Hello, Auntie.

119
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:35,280
Gao Bin is truly something.

120
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,700
He just couldn't get over her when he was young.

121
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:38,580
In the end, he still brought her child here.

122
00:06:38,580 --> 00:06:40,360
What are you talking about?

123
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,900
- You... Why are you tugging me?
- She's not here!

124
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:45,739
I just want to see if she's in the car! I see you!

125
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:47,570
- I see you! Come out!
- I'm sorry. Move.

126
00:06:47,570 --> 00:06:49,290
Why did you push me?

127
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:52,320
Get out of the car!

128
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,823
Start the car.

129
00:06:56,260 --> 00:06:58,519
Son, look sharp on that day, okay?

130
00:06:58,519 --> 00:06:59,700
Who says I'm going?

131
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:01,579
Gao Yang won't be there!

132
00:07:07,242 --> 00:07:14,922
[Episode 26: It's Hard to Accept and Feel It]

133
00:07:14,922 --> 00:07:16,210
[Wedding Invitation From Anna and Zhan Chonghai]

134
00:07:16,210 --> 00:07:21,580
October 1st, 2005, Saturday.

135
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:25,300
- Gao Yang, is Auntie An really getting married?
- Yes.

136
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,460
Then do I need to go?

137
00:07:27,460 --> 00:07:28,680
Wait, why would you go there?

138
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,659
Exactly, how does it concern you?

139
00:07:30,659 --> 00:07:33,940
No, I mean

140
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:37,859
Auntie An watched me grow up too. She found happiness again.

141
00:07:37,859 --> 00:07:41,060
Shouldn't our family attend and give her a wedding gift?

142
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:43,140
I'm not even going. Why should you go?

143
00:07:43,140 --> 00:07:45,020
Besides, she's so rich.

144
00:07:45,020 --> 00:07:46,460
She doesn't need anything else.

145
00:07:46,460 --> 00:07:47,979
- Then I won't go either.
- Zhan...

146
00:07:47,979 --> 00:07:50,859
should we pronounce this "Chong" or "Zhong"?
(T/N: There are two pronunciations for this character)

147
00:07:50,859 --> 00:07:53,999
Pronounce it however you want. It doesn't matter.

148
00:07:53,999 --> 00:07:55,539
Don't you want to know?

149
00:07:55,539 --> 00:07:57,800
After your mom marries him,

150
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:58,959
what should you call him?

151
00:07:58,959 --> 00:08:00,920
I'll call him whatever I want.

152
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:03,560
In a legal sense,

153
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,114
he's sort of your dad too.

154
00:08:14,179 --> 00:08:17,060
Look, are these the three characters?

155
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:18,742
Not that "Chong".
(T/N: He wrote a different character meaning esteemed, worship, lofty)

156
00:08:22,979 --> 00:08:25,759
It's this "Chong." "Chong" as in bigamy.

157
00:08:25,759 --> 00:08:27,736
I saw it on the invitation.

158
00:08:28,639 --> 00:08:32,379
I thought since Anna is hosting her wedding ceremony in Tieyuan,

159
00:08:32,379 --> 00:08:35,019
that man is probably from Tieyuan too.

160
00:08:36,946 --> 00:08:38,696
His name sounds familiar,

161
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,020
very familiar.

162
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:44,179
I think he's our peer.

163
00:08:44,179 --> 00:08:45,979
He's a teacher?

164
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:51,742
- Vice Principle.
- What is it?

165
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:57,440
- You did it?
- Yes.

166
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,119
Nice job.

167
00:08:59,119 --> 00:09:00,659
You've quietly took care an important matter.

168
00:09:00,659 --> 00:09:03,300
I'm getting older. I can't put it off anymore.
[Wedding Invitation from Wu Dibao and Yang Li]

169
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:05,697
- You must come on that day.
- I will, I will.

170
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:08,800
- Congratulations!
- Thank you, Vice Principal.

171
00:09:09,519 --> 00:09:13,660
You're teaching the Seniors and busily preparing to get married. It must be very tiring, right?

172
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:17,699
Oh, my goodness. Let me tell you... Not at all!

173
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:20,200
I'm keeping everything low key and minimalistic.

174
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,399
I won't let it affect my work.

175
00:09:21,399 --> 00:09:23,100
- Good, good.
- Don't worry, Vice Principal.

176
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:25,020
- I'll be on my way then.
- Okay.

177
00:09:27,179 --> 00:09:28,739
Wait a minute.

178
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:32,360
Try to avoid Bin when you see him later.

179
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,679
Why?

180
00:09:33,679 --> 00:09:35,500
I think he's acting a bit strange.

181
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:36,659
What happened to him?

182
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:40,260
His ex-wife is getting married again right in Tieyuan.

183
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,500
He's been feeling awkward all morning because he wasn't invited.

184
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,140
Why would his ex-wife invite him to her wedding?

185
00:09:44,140 --> 00:09:46,295
That's why I said he's acting strange.

186
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:49,500
Should I invite him then?

187
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:51,699
Why do I think you're acting strange too?

188
00:09:51,699 --> 00:09:53,020
Invite him if you like.

189
00:09:53,020 --> 00:09:54,900
What does it have to do with you?

190
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,639
You're right.

191
00:09:56,639 --> 00:09:59,460
Okay, thank you, Vice Principal. I'm leaving then.

192
00:10:01,639 --> 00:10:04,700
That Zhan Chonghai

193
00:10:05,419 --> 00:10:10,759
was once an English Teacher at the No. 2 Tie Yuan High School.

194
00:10:11,399 --> 00:10:17,279
A decade ago, he quit his job and started his own business in Beijing.

195
00:10:17,279 --> 00:10:21,279
He established an English training school. I heard he's doing pretty well.

196
00:10:21,279 --> 00:10:23,960
How well? Better than Anna?

197
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,999
Not as well as Anna.

198
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:30,179
He's a few years younger than Anna.

199
00:10:30,779 --> 00:10:33,539
I knew it!

200
00:10:33,539 --> 00:10:35,119
He's just a boy toy.

201
00:10:35,119 --> 00:10:36,779
Don't say that.

202
00:10:36,779 --> 00:10:39,339
At least he's a business owner.

203
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:46,420
Look at you, jealousy makes a man repulsive.

204
00:10:48,419 --> 00:10:50,020
I'm fine with that.

205
00:10:52,740 --> 00:10:54,497
Well, does he...

206
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,636
What?

207
00:10:58,579 --> 00:11:00,120
Does he have children?

208
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:02,760
This I really don't know about.

209
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:07,700
But I heard he's an amiable and cordial person.

210
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,620
The students like him a lot,

211
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:12,372
or else his business won't be that successful, right?

212
00:11:15,140 --> 00:11:18,439
Alright, got it.

213
00:11:19,459 --> 00:11:20,921
Bin,

214
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:28,720
don't cause a scene at their wedding, okay?

215
00:11:32,679 --> 00:11:34,620
- Hello, Mr. Wu.
- Hello, Mr. Wu.

216
00:11:44,539 --> 00:11:46,417
Mr. Wu.

217
00:11:46,417 --> 00:11:47,819
B-Brother Bin.

218
00:11:47,819 --> 00:11:49,643
What are you doing?

219
00:11:51,179 --> 00:11:53,140
I'm standing for a while. M-My back hurts from sitting.

220
00:11:53,140 --> 00:11:54,620
I'm standing for a while.

221
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,480
What are you hiding?

222
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,779
I'm not hiding anything. Nothing.

223
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:05,560
By the way, give back the class you took from me this afternoon.

224
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:07,179
I'm going to teach PE.

225
00:12:07,179 --> 00:12:09,440
Yes, right. We must have PE. We must.

226
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:11,620
Everyone steals from me.

227
00:12:11,620 --> 00:12:13,385
They take everything from me.

228
00:12:21,779 --> 00:12:23,900
Did he swallow gunpowder?

229
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:31,372
Are you going to the wedding?

230
00:12:36,819 --> 00:12:38,260
You haven't decided yet?

231
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:40,100
I'm not going.

232
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:44,739
One Gao Bin is enough for me.

233
00:12:44,739 --> 00:12:47,279
Why must Anna find me another one?

234
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:50,100
If you go, it's nothing but a meal.

235
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:54,020
She just invited me and not you and Gao Bin.

236
00:12:54,020 --> 00:12:56,179
How awkward would it be if I go alone?

237
00:12:56,919 --> 00:12:59,779
Third Uncle should be going.

238
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:02,027
I'm not going no matter who's going.

239
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,900
The wedding will go on without me anyway.

240
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:13,199
Besides, Anna never told me when she met this guy or when she planned to get married either.

241
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:16,380
She's not including me in major events in her life.

242
00:13:16,380 --> 00:13:18,420
Why should I celebrate it for her?

243
00:13:19,260 --> 00:13:20,775
Fine,

244
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:24,200
as long as you've made up your mind.

245
00:13:30,659 --> 00:13:33,040
I'll play video games with you for a while after school.

246
00:13:33,579 --> 00:13:37,620
Really? For at least an hour then.

247
00:13:37,620 --> 00:13:38,799
Half an hour.

248
00:13:38,799 --> 00:13:40,779
The console isn't even warm in half an hour.

249
00:13:40,779 --> 00:13:43,419
I'm not playing anymore. I'm going back home to do homework.

250
00:13:43,419 --> 00:13:45,260
How about 45 minutes then?

251
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:46,419
30.

252
00:13:46,419 --> 00:13:48,419
Then how about 30... 35?

253
00:13:48,419 --> 00:13:49,440
30.

254
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,440
33?

255
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,311
30.

256
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:56,879
You are my son after all.

257
00:13:56,879 --> 00:13:58,919
You look pretty handsome after you dress up.

258
00:13:58,919 --> 00:14:00,220
Am I right, Xiaowen?

259
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:02,600
It's just that the style is a bit old-fashioned.

260
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,440
How is this called old-fashioned? It's called classic.

261
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,600
It was tailor-made.

262
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,840
What classic?

263
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,440
Why did you ask me to wear this?

264
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:10,080
Aren't you going to your mom's wedding?

265
00:14:10,080 --> 00:14:11,639
You're the image of our family.

266
00:14:11,639 --> 00:14:12,740
Don't look too disheveled.

267
00:14:12,740 --> 00:14:16,819
After Secretary Yang came to our place and saw the house in a filthy state, he must've told your mom about it.

268
00:14:16,819 --> 00:14:19,280
You have to turn our image around.

269
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:21,059
This is too old. I'm not wearing it.

270
00:14:21,059 --> 00:14:22,140
Put... put it on.

271
00:14:22,140 --> 00:14:24,914
- I'm not wearing it. I'm not wearing it.
- It looks nice.

272
00:14:29,260 --> 00:14:31,877
- I'm not wearing it.
- Gao Yang, listen to me.

273
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:35,640
Your mom's boyfriend is quite something.

274
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:38,020
When you get there, he'll surely cozy up to you.

275
00:14:38,020 --> 00:14:41,380
Do not fall for his sugar-coated bullets.

276
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:45,259
When you get there, just sit down and eat. Eat the most expensive dishes. Don't say a word to him.

277
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:48,000
- Mr. Gao,
- You think I don't know?

278
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,699
I don't know who this is from.

279
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:55,559
National Day benefits!

280
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:59,279
- Not bad, not bad!
- It's such a big box!

281
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:08,269
Zhan Chonghai?
[Respectfully From: Zhan Chonghai]

282
00:15:08,269 --> 00:15:11,920
What did I say? Here comes a sugar-coated bullet.

283
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:14,799
Look at this. Look at this.

284
00:15:14,799 --> 00:15:17,319
This is what I call "clothes".

285
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:21,020
I must look handsome in it.

286
00:15:26,679 --> 00:15:27,900
What do you think?

287
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:29,706
It's just a bit too small.

288
00:15:29,706 --> 00:15:31,819
What do you think? Do I look handsome?

289
00:15:31,819 --> 00:15:34,120
Gao Bin, hurry up and take a look.

290
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,879
Look at you.

291
00:15:38,879 --> 00:15:40,939
I never said I'm going.

292
00:15:41,679 --> 00:15:43,020
You're not going?

293
00:15:43,020 --> 00:15:44,839
I don't want to go.

294
00:15:45,799 --> 00:15:51,374
Well... that's not right. That would make me seem so petty.

295
00:15:51,374 --> 00:15:56,219
Besides, the resentment between your mom and I are... are a thing of the past. It has nothing to do with you.

296
00:15:56,219 --> 00:15:57,600
You don't have to worry about my feelings.

297
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:00,719
You're overthinking. I just don't want to go.

298
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:06,060
If I do whatever he says and wear whatever he wants me to wear, that would be so embarrassing!

299
00:16:06,060 --> 00:16:07,639
I have my own personality, okay?

300
00:16:07,639 --> 00:16:09,939
That's my boy.

301
00:16:10,679 --> 00:16:11,720
- Here.
- Okay, okay.

302
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:14,000
- Keep these clothes for yourself.
- All right, all right.

303
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,858
Gao Yang,

304
00:16:16,879 --> 00:16:17,819
what about the new clothes?

305
00:16:17,819 --> 00:16:19,000
We must mail it back to him.

306
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,120
The Gao Family does not accept handouts and charity!

307
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,860
That's right! A man of integrity!

308
00:16:22,860 --> 00:16:24,920
Let's go play video games.

309
00:16:31,059 --> 00:16:33,205
It's such a waste to mail them back.

310
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:36,740
The clothes are too short for you!

311
00:16:36,740 --> 00:16:40,279
If it's too short, I can just alter it.

312
00:16:46,699 --> 00:16:48,179
Auntie, you're home.

313
00:16:48,179 --> 00:16:49,840
W-Why did you come home so late?

314
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:52,020
I went to the post office.

315
00:16:52,020 --> 00:16:55,819
Quickly take a look. It's for you.

316
00:16:57,899 --> 00:16:59,980
I-It's from Uncle Daqiang?

317
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,325
Let me see.

318
00:17:03,325 --> 00:17:06,771
- Slow down, don't cut your hand.
- Okay.

319
00:17:11,519 --> 00:17:12,939
An MP3 player?

320
00:17:12,939 --> 00:17:15,301
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

321
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:19,480
H-How's Uncle Daqiang doing in the South?

322
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:20,599
He's alright.

323
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:22,739
He finally found a real job.

324
00:17:22,739 --> 00:17:26,259
From now on, he can live a stable and honest life.

325
00:17:26,939 --> 00:17:28,419
W-What is this?

326
00:17:28,419 --> 00:17:33,419
Textbooks. We sent them to the orphanage but they were all returned to us.

327
00:17:33,419 --> 00:17:36,860
Take a look. Did we put down the wrong address?

328
00:17:36,860 --> 00:17:38,629
Let me see.

329
00:17:41,179 --> 00:17:46,340
It's the r-right address. I s-sent things there every time. How could it be wrong?

330
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:48,699
Then what happened?

331
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:54,559
I-I'll ask Xiaowen when I go to school tomorrow.

332
00:17:54,559 --> 00:17:58,759
Xiaowen, can you take a look and see if I wrote down the correct address?

333
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:02,511
Yes, it's right.

334
00:18:02,511 --> 00:18:07,020
Then w-w-why did they return the package I sent?

335
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:08,960
When did you mail it?

336
00:18:10,060 --> 00:18:12,340
Last week.

337
00:18:12,340 --> 00:18:15,699
It was fine when I sent them something last month.

338
00:18:15,699 --> 00:18:19,100
Did the orphanage move and didn't tell us?

339
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:20,857
That's not possible.

340
00:18:20,857 --> 00:18:23,849
They would surely notify us if anything happens at the orphanage.

341
00:18:24,739 --> 00:18:27,720
Then w-what's going on?

342
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:33,520
Let's call the orphanage.

343
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:35,081
Okay.

344
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,039
Mr. Wu.

345
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:45,640
Shush. Be quiet. Don't let him hear us.

346
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:46,559
Why?

347
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:48,844
Here.

348
00:18:48,844 --> 00:18:50,295
Mr. Wang,

349
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,994
here's yours.

350
00:18:52,994 --> 00:18:54,559
I'll leave it with him.

351
00:18:54,559 --> 00:18:55,459
Please come.

352
00:18:55,459 --> 00:18:57,359
- You're getting married?
- Yes.

353
00:18:57,359 --> 00:18:59,519
I'm afraid he will find out.

354
00:18:59,519 --> 00:19:00,900
Yes, you're right.

355
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:02,880
No wonder he had a long face yesterday.

356
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:03,839
His ex-wife is getting married.

357
00:19:03,839 --> 00:19:06,279
Yes, on the same day as my wedding.

358
00:19:06,279 --> 00:19:07,559
That's so awkward.

359
00:19:07,559 --> 00:19:09,500
Who's awkward?

360
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:15,799
Old Wu, what are you doing?

361
00:19:15,799 --> 00:19:17,480
My... My sh-shoelaces are untied.

362
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:20,448
Why are you sneaking around if your shoe laces are untied?

363
00:19:25,559 --> 00:19:26,880
Who's getting married?

364
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,580
You're getting married?

365
00:19:28,580 --> 00:19:30,839
Why didn't you invite me?

366
00:19:30,839 --> 00:19:32,459
I'm afraid of irritating you.

367
00:19:32,459 --> 00:19:34,799
Why would it irritate me?

368
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:37,039
Isn't that someone also...?

369
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:40,019
Anna?

370
00:19:40,019 --> 00:19:42,580
I moved on a long time ago.

371
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:46,779
Although I'm single, I have a good son.

372
00:19:46,779 --> 00:19:49,320
My son really cares about me.

373
00:19:49,979 --> 00:19:54,879
Old Wu, you should have kids as soon as possible after you get married.

374
00:19:54,879 --> 00:19:57,579
It might be hard and tiring to raise a child, but it's worth it.

375
00:19:57,579 --> 00:19:59,079
I... I'll do that soon.

376
00:19:59,079 --> 00:20:00,240
I'll be there for your wedding

377
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,659
and give you a big red envelope.

378
00:20:01,659 --> 00:20:03,291
Thank you, Brother Bin.

379
00:20:07,599 --> 00:20:10,119
Why was he pretending to sleep?

380
00:20:13,079 --> 00:20:15,640
Sorry, the number you've dialed is no longer in service.

381
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:16,792
What's wrong?

382
00:20:16,792 --> 00:20:18,839
It's no longer in service.

383
00:20:28,900 --> 00:20:30,979
Hello, who is it?

384
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:32,815
Director, it's me, Xiaowen.

385
00:20:32,815 --> 00:20:36,348
Xiaowen? What's wrong?

386
00:20:36,348 --> 00:20:40,119
Why is the land line of our orphanage out of service?

387
00:20:40,620 --> 00:20:44,860
No, no, everyone is using cellphones now.

388
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:47,659
The land line is useless, so we cancelled it.

389
00:20:47,659 --> 00:20:51,680
From now on, just call my cellphone if you need anything, okay?

390
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:55,439
Then how come the package Mi Jia sent was returned as well?

391
00:20:55,439 --> 00:20:59,000
Did our orphanage move to another location?

392
00:20:59,970 --> 00:21:01,640
I asked them to return it.

393
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:03,940
We're renovating the orphanage lately.

394
00:21:03,940 --> 00:21:06,580
It's not convenient to receive it.

395
00:21:06,580 --> 00:21:08,860
You don't need to send them anymore, okay?

396
00:21:08,860 --> 00:21:12,720
- I'll tell you when the renovation is complete.
 - Okay.

397
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,739
Then, do you need our help?

398
00:21:14,739 --> 00:21:18,540
Xiaowen, the two of you are Seniors now.

399
00:21:18,540 --> 00:21:23,500
You and Mi Jia should just focus on your studies and training.

400
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,380
You don't need to worry about us.

401
00:21:25,380 --> 00:21:28,499
Your elder brothers and sisters are taking good care of us.

402
00:21:28,499 --> 00:21:33,360
After you graduate, you can come back to help if you want, okay?

403
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:35,259
Okay, Director.

404
00:21:35,259 --> 00:21:38,519
Make sure to let us know if there's anything.

405
00:21:38,519 --> 00:21:39,659
Sure, sure.

406
00:21:39,659 --> 00:21:43,060
Don't worry. I'm hanging up now.

407
00:21:50,679 --> 00:21:52,559
What did she say?

408
00:21:52,559 --> 00:21:56,480
She said they're doing renovations.

409
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:58,399
Renovations?

410
00:21:58,970 --> 00:22:03,279
Does our orphanage have money to renovate?

411
00:22:14,010 --> 00:22:17,140
Jia, what exactly is going on?

412
00:22:17,140 --> 00:22:21,400
You didn't eat lunch at the cafeteria and you've been distracted during class.

413
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:24,359
N-N-Nothing.

414
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:27,615
Xiaowen,

415
00:22:28,259 --> 00:22:29,780
where's Gao Yang?

416
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:31,340
He's in the restroom.

417
00:22:31,340 --> 00:22:33,659
Why is he going again?

418
00:22:33,659 --> 00:22:35,780
Don't worry, Mi Jia.

419
00:22:36,259 --> 00:22:38,699
Let's go back when we're on vacation.

420
00:22:38,699 --> 00:22:40,120
- Coming! Coming!
- Okay.

421
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:42,840
- Where are you going?
- The orphanage.

422
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:44,791
What orphanage?

423
00:22:47,140 --> 00:22:50,459
Eat less! How many times do you poop each day? Let's go.

424
00:22:50,459 --> 00:22:52,413
What?

425
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:57,119
Xiaowen, what's wrong with the orphanage?

426
00:22:58,140 --> 00:22:59,887
Talk to me about it.

427
00:23:01,970 --> 00:23:05,059
This car is so shiny.

428
00:23:05,059 --> 00:23:06,659
It's "Jing A" (Beijing license plate).

429
00:23:06,659 --> 00:23:09,060
Is it Auntie An's car?

430
00:23:09,459 --> 00:23:10,979
My mom drives a BMW.

431
00:23:10,979 --> 00:23:12,499
Then let me go and take a look.

432
00:23:12,499 --> 00:23:14,799
Don't scratch it.

433
00:23:14,799 --> 00:23:18,139
I can use his car a mirror!

434
00:23:20,119 --> 00:23:21,540
I'm sorry, Uncle.

435
00:23:21,540 --> 00:23:22,659
Let's hurry up and leave.

436
00:23:22,659 --> 00:23:24,127
Wait a minute.

437
00:23:26,340 --> 00:23:27,780
- Hello.
- Hello.

438
00:23:27,780 --> 00:23:29,619
You're Gao Yang, right?

439
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:32,219
You are?

440
00:23:32,219 --> 00:23:35,280
I forgot to introduce myself. I'm your Uncle Zhan.

441
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:37,055
Uncle what?

442
00:23:37,540 --> 00:23:40,780
Your mom and I will be married in a few days.

443
00:23:46,380 --> 00:23:50,540
Have a drink first. I'll go set up the stall. I'll make kabobs for you when I come back.

444
00:23:57,340 --> 00:24:00,360
Why don't I treat you somewhere else?

445
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:02,939
No need. Just quickly say it.

446
00:24:06,140 --> 00:24:10,020
Us getting remarried is indeed quite sudden.

447
00:24:10,020 --> 00:24:15,219
I think I should meet you and your dad before we get married.

448
00:24:15,219 --> 00:24:19,559
I wanted to come with your mom, but we never had the chance.

449
00:24:19,559 --> 00:24:23,219
Therefore, I just came unannounced today.

450
00:24:23,674 --> 00:24:24,939
I didn't disturb you, did I?

451
00:24:24,939 --> 00:24:26,300
Yes, you did.

452
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:29,319
We're about to take the college entrance exams. We're very busy.

453
00:24:30,119 --> 00:24:32,539
Uncle, he didn't mean that.

454
00:24:32,539 --> 00:24:35,180
It's okay, it's okay. I can understand. Truly,

455
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:36,788
I can understand.

456
00:24:39,035 --> 00:24:42,880
In a reconstituted family, the children are bound to feel upset.

457
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:46,140
We can slowly get to know each other. It will surely get better in the future.

458
00:24:46,140 --> 00:24:47,933
Who wants to get along with you?

459
00:24:52,699 --> 00:24:55,739
Gao Yang, This is for you.

460
00:24:57,210 --> 00:24:59,259
I'm leaving if there's nothing else.

461
00:25:00,180 --> 00:25:02,192
I'll see you at the wedding then.

462
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:04,580
Who says I'm going to your wedding?

463
00:25:04,580 --> 00:25:07,839
Gao Yang, your mom really wants you to be there.

464
00:25:07,839 --> 00:25:10,499
Uncle, please don't pressure him anymore.

465
00:25:10,499 --> 00:25:15,919
That's right, Uncle. Children don't really have to attend their parent's weddings, right?

466
00:25:17,499 --> 00:25:20,659
Uncle, I don't oppose you marrying my mom.

467
00:25:20,659 --> 00:25:22,439
That's your business.

468
00:25:22,439 --> 00:25:24,214
But I don't want to go.

469
00:25:24,780 --> 00:25:26,700
Gao Yang.

470
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,306
Gao Yang!

471
00:25:30,540 --> 00:25:33,179
Gao Yang, take this.

472
00:25:33,179 --> 00:25:35,240
- I don't want it.
- It's my gift to you.

473
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:38,579
Who are you? Why are you following my son?

474
00:25:39,540 --> 00:25:41,013
Brother Bin.

475
00:25:41,419 --> 00:25:43,119
Who are you?

476
00:25:43,119 --> 00:25:45,179
You don't remember me?

477
00:25:46,140 --> 00:25:48,319
We met in Beijing.

478
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:53,328
You're here to see Anna too?

479
00:25:54,839 --> 00:25:56,119
It's you.

480
00:25:56,119 --> 00:25:57,659
- What's your name?
- Zhan Chonghai.

481
00:25:57,659 --> 00:26:00,219
So it's you! What's wrong with you?

482
00:26:00,219 --> 00:26:03,300
Why did you come to my house? Gao Yang is not going to the wedding, understand?

483
00:26:03,300 --> 00:26:05,280
He already told me.

484
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:06,820
I really do understand.

485
00:26:06,820 --> 00:26:14,520
Brother Bin, it's not easy for you to raise Gao Yang for so many years by yourself.

486
00:26:15,970 --> 00:26:17,883
It was alright.

487
00:26:17,883 --> 00:26:21,599
Brother Bin, thank you for your trust.

488
00:26:21,599 --> 00:26:25,259
I will surely take good care of Gao Yang after he arrives in Beijing.

489
00:26:25,259 --> 00:26:26,950
Don't worry.

490
00:26:27,259 --> 00:26:28,480
I'll be on my way then.

491
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:30,054
Wait a minute.

492
00:26:30,780 --> 00:26:32,780
Why is Gao Yang going to Beijing?

493
00:26:32,780 --> 00:26:34,820
Didn't Anna tell you?

494
00:26:34,820 --> 00:26:40,279
- After the wedding, Anna and I will bring Gao Yang to Beijing with us.
- What?

495
00:26:43,250 --> 00:26:44,837
Brother Bin,

496
00:26:47,380 --> 00:26:49,085
this is for Gao Yang.

497
00:26:51,419 --> 00:26:56,004
Give me a call if there's anything. I'm leaving now.

498
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:04,780
Half a year ago, you said you'll take Gao Yang away.

499
00:27:04,780 --> 00:27:06,540
You changed your mind halfway through.

500
00:27:06,540 --> 00:27:08,860
Now, you say you want to take Gao Yang away again.

501
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:12,219
What? Are you playing with us?

502
00:27:12,219 --> 00:27:13,960
To think I even put in a good word for you.

503
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:16,419
It's not the same now as it was half a year ago.

504
00:27:16,419 --> 00:27:19,100
What's not the same?

505
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:21,299
At least you notified me in advance half a year ago. Now you...

506
00:27:21,299 --> 00:27:26,050
Now, if it wasn't that... If that Zhan Chonghai didn't tell me, I wouldn't even know!

507
00:27:26,059 --> 00:27:27,659
What do you mean by this?

508
00:27:27,659 --> 00:27:30,060
Are you going to kidnap Gao Yang at the wedding?

509
00:27:30,060 --> 00:27:34,160
- I can't talk to you when you're this emotional. I'm hanging up.
- Don't you hang up on me!

510
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:35,900
Gao Yang will not go with you!

511
00:27:35,900 --> 00:27:40,120
What do you mean? If he doesn't come with me, will he stay with you or with that Ye Xiaowen?

512
00:27:40,120 --> 00:27:44,859
Wait, what does that have to do with Xiaowen? Anna, I'm telling you...

513
00:27:44,859 --> 00:27:48,299
Hello, I'm Gao Yang. I'll see you at the wedding.

514
00:27:52,300 --> 00:27:53,860
Why are you going again?

515
00:27:53,860 --> 00:27:57,659
Didn't she ask who I'm going to live with? I'll show her.

516
00:27:57,659 --> 00:28:00,540
Well, let's get ourselves some nice clothes.

517
00:28:00,540 --> 00:28:01,739
The three of us will go together.

518
00:28:01,739 --> 00:28:04,580
All right, I'll go get ready then.

519
00:28:08,359 --> 00:28:10,480
Did she misunderstand something?

520
00:28:11,340 --> 00:28:12,699
That silly girl.

521
00:28:12,699 --> 00:28:14,540
Xiaowen, let's go together.

522
00:28:14,540 --> 00:28:16,140
I... I'm going too?

523
00:28:16,140 --> 00:28:19,579
Yes, we're all indispensable. The three of us are family.

524
00:28:19,579 --> 00:28:21,019
That's more like it!

525
00:28:21,019 --> 00:28:23,580
Let's go get some clothes.

526
00:28:33,522 --> 00:28:34,662
[Happy Wedding]

527
00:28:34,662 --> 00:28:37,442
[Harmonious Union For A Hundred Years]

528
00:29:02,900 --> 00:29:05,219
Wish Anna a happy marriage.

529
00:29:05,219 --> 00:29:08,619
You're in the wrong place. It's the next table.

530
00:29:17,450 --> 00:29:19,100
Sorry about that.

531
00:29:19,100 --> 00:29:20,854
What a perfect match.

532
00:29:20,854 --> 00:29:28,234
[Tieyuan Three Brothers]

533
00:29:28,234 --> 00:29:30,127
Please head upstairs.

534
00:29:31,940 --> 00:29:34,340
- Save your stomach for the feast.
- And take some home.

535
00:29:34,340 --> 00:29:37,005
My friend gave me this. Put it away for me.

536
00:29:37,005 --> 00:29:38,969
Yang Yang,

537
00:29:38,969 --> 00:29:42,580
Brother Bin, you... Why are you all here?

538
00:29:42,580 --> 00:29:45,459
It's my mom's wedding. We have to be here.

539
00:29:45,860 --> 00:29:48,459
Congratulations, I wish you a happy marriage together.

540
00:29:48,459 --> 00:29:50,114
I'm returning the computer.

541
00:29:51,930 --> 00:29:55,139
Anna has a bad temper. Please bear with her.

542
00:29:55,759 --> 00:29:57,310
Congratulations.

543
00:30:03,960 --> 00:30:06,480
This lipstick color is okay, right?

544
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:08,045
Yes.

545
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:12,320
Why are you in such a panic?

546
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:14,234
Gao Yang is here.

547
00:30:16,010 --> 00:30:19,019
Look at how nervous you are. He shouldn't be here?

548
00:30:19,019 --> 00:30:22,000
Brother Bin and that boy are here, too.

549
00:30:24,580 --> 00:30:27,919
They are already here. I can't just kick them out.

550
00:30:32,790 --> 00:30:35,260
Calm down. It's our wedding day.

551
00:30:35,260 --> 00:30:38,419
Anna, calm down.

552
00:30:38,419 --> 00:30:39,900
Stay out of this.

553
00:30:39,900 --> 00:30:42,920
But this is our wedding day.

554
00:30:47,219 --> 00:30:50,299
Xiaowen, keep calm, keep calm.

555
00:30:50,299 --> 00:30:52,959
These are all cold dishes. They're cheap. Let's wait for the hot dishes.

556
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:56,059
When the lobster and abalones come, we'll eat our money's worth.

557
00:30:56,059 --> 00:31:00,260
Just drink this later. This is the most expensive drink.

558
00:31:05,870 --> 00:31:09,080
Third Uncle, why do you keep staring at me?

559
00:31:09,080 --> 00:31:10,880
- Is there something on my face?
- No.

560
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:14,859
Bin, you won't act impulsively, right?

561
00:31:14,859 --> 00:31:15,780
What's there to be impulsive about?

562
00:31:15,780 --> 00:31:20,060
Actually, it's not easy for Anna to remarry after being single for so many years.

563
00:31:20,060 --> 00:31:22,580
Don't cause a scene.

564
00:31:22,580 --> 00:31:26,780
Third Uncle, don't worry. I'm here to congratulate her.

565
00:31:26,780 --> 00:31:29,620
Besides, I'm mainly here for Gao Yang.

566
00:31:29,620 --> 00:31:33,800
If there's a knot in my heart, I wouldn't have come, right?

567
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:36,300
Third Uncle, let me tell you...

568
00:31:36,300 --> 00:31:38,714
My mom's here. My mom's here.

569
00:31:38,714 --> 00:31:40,080
Gao Bin.

570
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:42,739
Gao Yang is a child, he doesn't understand etiquette. Do you not understand that as well?

571
00:31:42,739 --> 00:31:45,300
Anna, don't act impulsively.

572
00:31:45,300 --> 00:31:46,499
It's your wedding day.

573
00:31:46,499 --> 00:31:47,599
Third Uncle, stay out of this.

574
00:31:47,599 --> 00:31:49,860
Anna, I'm here to congratulate you.

575
00:31:49,860 --> 00:31:51,439
- Can you stay calm?
- You think I don't know you?

576
00:31:51,439 --> 00:31:52,920
Say no more.

577
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:54,620
Brother Bin is already here.

578
00:31:54,620 --> 00:31:56,459
Brother Bin, enjoy the food and drinks.

579
00:31:56,459 --> 00:31:58,100
Okay, okay.

580
00:31:58,100 --> 00:31:59,720
Fine, eat.

581
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:02,680
It's your last meal with your son anyway.

582
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:05,260
Gao Yang, we're leaving tonight.

583
00:32:05,260 --> 00:32:07,148
Who says I'm leaving?

584
00:32:07,148 --> 00:32:08,813
I'm not leaving.

585
00:32:14,410 --> 00:32:16,367
Say that again?

586
00:32:16,780 --> 00:32:19,259
Haven't you been asking me who I'm going to stay with in Tieyuan?

587
00:32:19,259 --> 00:32:24,039
My dad, Gao Bin, and my younger brother, Ye Xiaowen. The three of us will live together.

588
00:32:33,140 --> 00:32:37,340
Gao Yang, I'll ask you one last time.

589
00:32:37,900 --> 00:32:39,693
Will you go with me?

590
00:32:42,900 --> 00:32:44,756
I'm not leaving.

591
00:32:44,756 --> 00:32:48,019
Anna, let's talk about this later.

592
00:32:48,019 --> 00:32:49,780
The ceremony is about to start. Everyone is waiting.

593
00:32:49,780 --> 00:32:51,839
The wedding is off!

594
00:32:53,410 --> 00:32:55,319
Come on. Come with me!

595
00:32:55,319 --> 00:32:57,568
- Wait, what are you doing?
- Let's go!

596
00:33:27,090 --> 00:33:33,250
♫ I know the direction of dawn ♫

597
00:33:33,250 --> 00:33:40,215
♫  It's right in front of me, waiting for me to shine  ♫

598
00:33:40,215 --> 00:33:46,505
♫  The starlight that shines alone the way  ♫

599
00:33:46,505 --> 00:33:52,545
♫  Accompanying me on my adventure, packing my dreams in my heart  ♫

600
00:33:52,545 --> 00:33:59,197
♫  I don't fear the rough journey ahead, I will no longer run away  ♫

601
00:33:59,197 --> 00:34:04,837
♫  Maybe I'm not destined for the hardship of this journey  ♫

602
00:34:04,837 --> 00:34:08,750
♫  To chase after the longing in my heart  ♫

603
00:34:08,750 --> 00:34:12,172
♫  Let's set sail on your dreams  ♫

604
00:34:12,172 --> 00:34:15,467
♫  Let's not have any regrets in our youth  ♫

605
00:34:15,467 --> 00:34:22,227
♫  Even if you stumble and fall, I'll be by your side  ♫

606
00:34:22,235 --> 00:34:25,438
♫  Let's find the answer through the madness  ♫

607
00:34:25,438 --> 00:34:29,650
♫  Let's have courage to ride the waves and billows  ♫

608
00:34:29,650 --> 00:34:33,470
♫  With my wings, I'll fly us to the future  ♫

609
00:34:33,470 --> 00:34:41,330
♫  And step forward into the future without fear of sorrow  ♫
